HEADWORD: Conductive
<hw>Con*duct"ive</hw> <pr>(-d⟦ucr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Having the quality or power of conducting; <as>as, the
<ex>conductive</ex> tissue of a pistil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ovarian walls . . . are seen to be distinctly
